The paper proposes a new stochastic algorithm for solving linear equations and nonlinear optimization problems, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization. The paper also includes experimental results on learning models and large-scale datasets, indicating that the algorithm is applicable to various machine learning tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
